content: In that case, a general definition for "natural" could be something that exists or occurs without the intervention of a supernatural or divine power, and that can be studied and explained through scientific observation, experimentation, and analysis. It encompasses all phenomena, entities, and processes that are observable and subject to the laws of nature. Examples of natural phenomena include the movements of celestial bodies, the behavior of subatomic particles, the growth and reproduction of living organisms, and the formation of geological structures.
